You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot application migrated to Java 21 Virtual Threads starts experiencing severe latency spikes and thread starvation under heavy load. Below is the suspect code snippet within a `@Service` bean:

java
@Service
public class CashService {
    private final Map<String, String> cache = new HashMap<>();

    public synchronized String getOrFetch(String key, Supplier<String> loader) {
        if (cache.containsKey(key)) {
            return cache.get(key);
        }
        String val = loader.get(); // Performs a blocking HTTP call
        cache.put(key, val);
        return val;
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where customer orders are occasionally failing to trigger email notifications, and database updates seem to be inconsistently visible. The implementation looks like this:

java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Autowired private OrderRepository repo;
    @Autowired private NotificationService notifier;

    @Transactional
    public void processOrder(Order order) {
        repo.save(order);
        CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
            notifier.sendEmail(order); // Reads order status from DB and sends email
        });
    } 
}

You are debugging a production issue where a service utilizing Java 21 Virtual Threads and a custom carrier thread pool size completely freezes and hangs indefinitely. The service throttles parallel integration calls using a `Semaphore` of 10 permits. Thousands of virtual threads execute the following code block concurrently:

java
public void callIntegration() {
    try {
        semaphore.acquire();
        synchronized (lock) {
            restClient.getForObject("https://api.thirdparty.com/v1/resource", String.class);
        }
    } catch (InterruptedException e) {
        Thread.currentThread().interrupt();
    } finally {
        semaphore.release();
    } 
}
